This paper deals with the problem of designing callout mechanisms for repeated auctions, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and information retrieval (cs.IR) aspects. The proposed framework also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, which fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and multimedia (cs.MM).
